    "instruction": "From error_logs.csv, filter rows where cmdb_id is in ['frontend-0','frontend-1','frontend-2'] AND timestamp between 2022-03-20 14:30:00 and 2022-03-20 14:35:00 UTC+8. Return:\n1) Up to the first 20 rows sorted by timestamp with columns: timestamp, cmdb_id, full message (do not truncate).\n2) A compact count of distinct full messages in that 5-minute slice (top 5 messages with counts).\nKeep outputs compact and do not return other raw time series."}

{
    "analysis": "We inspected metrics, traces, and logs for frontends. Key findings so far: all three frontend pods (frontend-0/1/2) started emitting repeated warning logs \"failed to retrieve ads\" beginning at 2022-03-20 14:30:00 UTC+8, and log.error_count confirms per-minute errors from that minute. Focused traces from frontends to adservice (trace.to_adservice.*) during the 14:30–15:00 window show nonzero row_count (traffic) but zero error_rate — i.e., adservice-facing traces did not report RPC errors. Metrics and traces contained many constant-zero KPIs that produced false-positive anomalies with the percentile rule and are therefore unreliable. The log evidence strongly implicates ad content retrieval failing at the frontend level, but adservice traces do not show increased error rates. To localize root cause (adservice vs network vs ad backend), we now need to check adservice-side logs and normalized per-minute log.error_count for adservice pods in the incident window, and confirm whether error_logs contains any adservice entries. This will tell us if adservice itself logged errors at or just before 14:30, or whether only frontends logged the warnings (suggesting an upstream ad backend or network issue).",
    "completed": "False",
    "instruction": "From log.csv and error_logs.csv do the following for adservice pods ['adservice-0','adservice-1','adservice-2','adservice2-0'] within the incident window March 20, 2022 14:30:00 to 15:00:00 UTC+8:\n1) log.csv: For each cmdb_id and log_name compute: points_in_window (count), sum_value_in_window, max_in_window, earliest_ts_where_value_gt_0 (or NULL). Limit output to these four pods and return compact rows (one row per cmdb_id/log_name).\n2) error_logs.csv: report whether any rows exist for these adservice cmdb_ids in the incident window; if any, return up to the first 10 rows with timestamp, cmdb_id, full message.\nReturn the compact aggregates and a one-line summary: whether adservice pods recorded errors in logs during the window and the earliest adservice-side error timestamp if present." }

